properties.name: The Swingin' Door
properties.comments: Swingin Door itself: 5 stars Friday karaoke with Roger: 5 stars Saturday karaoke with DJ Purple: 1 star

properties.name: Britannia Arms
properties.comments: I've been here many, many times on Wednesday nights and the occasional Sunday night for karaoke.  The crowd is usually pretty good and there is often a fine selection of womenfolk (as Bay Area bars go).  The current KJ's have a much better setup/song

properties.name: Goosetown Lounge
properties.comments: This lounge is adjacent to a nice Italian restaurant.  It's somewhat on the small side and can get pretty crowded but there are lots of tables and the waitresses are pretty attentive.  The bartenders also seem to be pretty quick.

properties.name: Almaden Lounge
properties.comments: The ugly-as-sin wooden statue of a topless mermaid near the door perfectly sums up the feel of this place.  It has a fisherman's theme for whatever reason and is buried in the back of a strip mall off of Blossom Hill.
properties.address: 1160 Blossom Hill Rd, San Jose, CA 95118

properties.name: The Kings Head Pub & Restaurant
